{"id":14881124,"mediaExerciseId":"3f115a1b-2337-4b59-86d6-2118cc3688a8","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"8","chapterTitle":"Stock Valuation","groupId":612321,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":265,"solutions":[{"id":6426827,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will discuss a trait of stocks very important to investors - the <b><span style=\"color: #4257B2\">required rate of return</span></b>.\n\nLet's get started!","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's start by explaining what the <b><span style=\"color: #4257B2\">required rate of return</span></b> is and how it's calculated.\n\nThe <b><span style=\"color: #4257B2\">required rate of return</span></b> **is the minimum return on investment that an investor expects to get.** \n\nEssentially, the <b><span style=\"color: #4257B2\">required rate of return</span></b> is the lowest acceptable reimbursement for the degree of risk in the investment. It is a crucial notion in stock valuation where it is widely used to assess the present value of cash flows.\n\nIt is calculated as the sum of dividend yield and the growth rate:\n\n$$\\text{RRR} = \\text{Dividend Yield} + \\text{Growth Rate} \\tag{1} $$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We are given the following information:\n\n1. Growth rate is 3.7%\n2. Dividend yield is 5.6%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"By inputting the given values into Eq.$(1)$, we calculate the <b><span style=\"color: #4257B2\">required rate of return</span></b>:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{RRR} &=  3.7\\% + 5.6\\%  \\\\[10pt]\n&= 9.3\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**Let's recap what we have done in this exercise!**\n\n\nFirst, we explained the key term of this exercise - the <b><span style=\"color: #4257B2\">required rate of return</span></b>.\n\nWe discussed its importance and presented a way to calculate it using the values given in the exercise text.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"28b0b62e-be6f-4485-a42c-2a9be72ad9a2","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881125,"exerciseName":"6","page":265,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"112e3c7f-0342-46ac-bd50-cb70756269b4","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-8-questions-and-problems-6-112e3c7f-0342-46ac-bd50-cb70756269b4"},{"id":14881126,"exerciseName":"7","page":266,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"12bc9739-91b6-4e14-a857-9b27042801ca","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-8-questions-and-problems-7-12bc9739-91b6-4e14-a857-9b27